PROJECT DESCRIPTION :
                    A Bank Management System is a software application designed to manage and automate the daily operations of a bank. It helps in handling customer accounts, transactions, and financial records efficiently and securely.
                   The system allows users (bank staff and customers) to perform various activities such as account creation, deposits, withdrawals, fund transfers, and balance inquiries. It also maintains accurate records of all transactions and customer details in a centralized database.
                   This system improves speed, accuracy, and security in banking operations while reducing manual work. It also provides features like loan management, interest calculation, report generation, and user authentication to ensure safe and reliable banking services.
                   Overall, a Bank Management System plays an important role in modern banking by making financial services faster, easier, and more accessible.
	

